items.title: Korean AI startup Motif reveals 4 big lessons for training enterprise LLMs
items.summary: Motif Technologies has released a new model that boasts impressive benchmark scores . It's the most performant model from that country according to an independent benchmarking lab Artificial Analysis . The company has published a white paper on arxiv.org with a concrete, reproducible training recipe . The paper offers a set of practical lessons about data alignment, long-context infrastructure, and reinforcement learning stability .

CUGa on Hugged Face: Hugging Facial AI Agents is a way of making AI agents more powerful and smarter .

items.title: Tokenization takes the lead in the fight for data security
items.summary: Tokenization is emerging as a cornerstone of modern data security, helping businesses separate the value of their data from its risk . It converts sensitive data into a nonsensitive digital replacement, called a token, that maps back to the original, which is secured in a digital vault . The token placeholder preserves both the format and the utility of the sensitive data, and can be used across applications — including AI models .

items.title: Why agentic AI needs a new category of customer data
items.summary: Twilio: The customer data infrastructure powering most enterprises was architected for a world that no longer exists . A fast-moving stream of conversational signals (tone, urgency, intent, sentiment) represents a fundamentally different category of customer data . The problem is that conversational AI requires real-time, portable memory of customer interactions . The result: customer experiences defined by repetition, friction, and disjointed handoffs .

items.title: Why most enterprise AI coding pilots underperform (Hint: It's not the model)
items.summary: Dhyey Mavani is accelerating generative AI at LinkedIn and is a guest author at VentureBeat . Despite excitement around “AI agents that code,” most enterprise deployments underperform . Enterprises must re-architect the workflows around these agents, he says . The limiting factor is no longer the model, it's the structure, history and intent surrounding the code being changed .
